records.addlTxt:
Defendant Andrew J Alles in court with Attorney Anthony D Cotton.  Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Counts #2 and 3 are dismissed and read-in.  Count #4 is dismissed by operation of law.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Cotton makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant has been accepted in Alcohol Treatment court.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  WITHHELD SENTENCE:   

*D/L REVOCATION:  34 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK:  34 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS  (1 Day credit, if revoked)

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia 
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 
*Victim Impact Panel (already completed)

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to  City of Waukesha Police Department);

FINE:  $2,277.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($2,000.00) -remainder due as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  240 DAYS  Non-working hours with standard release conditions to commence forthwith. Defendant taken into custody.
